metadata.indicator_name: Total Annual Gross Domestic Product (GDP) at current prices in dolllars
metadata.definition:
The Gross Domestic Product (GDP) is the value of the flow of goods and servicies in a country at market prices, for each year during a pre-determined reference period. The figures are in United States dollars, utilizing the exchange rate published by ECLAC.
Regional and subregional totals based on available data for the countries of the region.
metadata.calculation_methodology: The methodology adopted for preparing the region's national accounts series at current prices consists of converting the series in national currency into current United States dollars, through the exchange rate published by the International Monetary Fund (rf series).
